-I didn't go in the house today.

04:08.900 --> 04:10.800
I didn't
go in the house today.

04:10.833 --> 04:12.867
-So what--
-I just want
to see my dog, dude.

04:12.900 --> 04:14.367
-I got that, man.
I can understand that.

04:14.400 --> 04:15.700
-She has my dog, dude.

04:15.733 --> 04:18.100
-What did you do?
-I don't know, I was trying

04:18.133 --> 04:21.200
to knock on the door...
(continues indistinct)

04:21.233 --> 04:23.400
I didn't do anything wrong.

04:23.433 --> 04:25.133
-Did you break some locks?
-No.

04:25.167 --> 04:28.067
I've lived there forever dude,
my keys are right here.

04:28.067 --> 04:29.233
-When did you move out?

04:29.267 --> 04:32.133
-She told me to leave,
like, two months ago.

04:32.167 --> 04:33.767
-What'd your sister
kick you out for?

04:33.800 --> 04:35.300
-Well,
you won't believe me, but--

04:35.333 --> 04:36.567
-Try me, come on.

04:36.600 --> 04:38.333
-My mom says menopause.

04:38.367 --> 04:43.200
I've been there forever, dude,
and I know I wasn't doing
nothing wrong, dude.

04:43.233 --> 04:45.267
-I just want to see my dog.

04:45.300 --> 04:46.800
I didn't do nothing wrong.

04:46.833 --> 04:48.600
-Okay.
-I didn't do nothing wrong.

04:48.633 --> 04:51.167
-Hey, when I asked you
to turn around,
why'd you--

04:51.200 --> 04:53.400
-I was mad because
I didn't do nothing wrong.

04:53.433 --> 04:56.500
That's why.
-Okay, but she's saying
you had, like, a crowbar.

04:56.533 --> 04:58.467
-No, I had a little, tiny bar.

04:58.500 --> 05:02.233
I mean, like a little
screwdriver, but my keys
are right here.

05:02.267 --> 05:04.267
Because I just wanted
to see my dog, bro.

05:04.300 --> 05:06.067
-You want to see your dog?
-It hurts me.

05:06.067 --> 05:07.633
(bleep) hurts me, dude.

05:07.667 --> 05:11.133
-What were you using
the screwdriver-crowbar for?

05:11.167 --> 05:13.067
-To try to get in, I guess.

05:13.100 --> 05:15.167
-Bein' an idiot.
-Okay.

05:15.200 --> 05:16.800
All right, well,
just sit tight for a minute.

05:18.500 --> 05:20.067
Sister:
We just don't
get along.

05:20.100 --> 05:22.667
But I felt sorry for him
because I didn't want him
on the streets.

05:22.700 --> 05:26.633
And you know, here I let him
stay with me for so long
and he takes advantage of me.

05:26.667 --> 05:28.667
So I'm just getting sick of it,
you know?

05:28.700 --> 05:30.967
It's like, I come home
and the house is a wreck.

05:31.067 --> 05:34.567
He doesn't do anything,
and it's like my stuff
is being destroyed.

05:34.600 --> 05:37.067
-Yeah.
-So-- And--

05:37.067 --> 05:38.433
-Completely understandable.

05:38.467 --> 05:40.933
-And you know,
and I-- I give him everything.

05:40.967 --> 05:42.900
It's like, he had a computer
to use during the day.

05:42.933 --> 05:45.633
And it's like,
he had a cell phone. So...

05:45.667 --> 05:47.067
-Can I see the damage?

05:47.100 --> 05:48.733
-So he's busted
both my locks

05:48.767 --> 05:50.067
and I just
had the locks changed.

05:50.100 --> 05:52.400
-Okay. Do you think
I could show him his dog
real quick?

05:52.433 --> 05:54.167
-Rascal's crazy.
-Can I give it a try?

05:54.200 --> 05:55.900
-Yeah. Rascal, come here.

05:55.933 --> 05:57.467
-Crazy like he's gonna
bite my hand off?

05:57.500 --> 05:59.333
-Yeah, he bites me
and he bites him.

05:59.367 --> 06:00.700
It's okay, it's okay.

06:00.733 --> 06:02.200
-Hey, buddy.
-It's okay.

06:02.233 --> 06:03.500
-Hey.

06:03.533 --> 06:04.800
-It's okay, it's okay.

06:04.833 --> 06:06.533
-You want
to come with me, buddy?

06:06.567 --> 06:07.767
-It's okay.

06:07.800 --> 06:09.467
-(Rascal growls)
-You can try to hold him
if you want.

06:09.500 --> 06:10.900
Yeah, but just
be careful.

06:10.933 --> 06:13.733
He's got long-- Ow!
-(dog snarls)

06:13.767 --> 06:15.167
Oh, my god. Ow.

06:15.200 --> 06:17.067
Rascal, it's okay.

06:17.100 --> 06:18.333
-Rascal,
you're all right, buddy.

06:18.367 --> 06:20.400
-I feel bad because
he should not
be going to jail.

06:20.433 --> 06:22.867
-Yeah, unfortunately,
he has to.

06:22.900 --> 06:27.533
So I'm going to give him
a last chance to see his dog
before he ends up going to jail.

06:27.567 --> 06:30.200
Hey, Michael, just wanted
to give you a chance to see
your dog real quick.

06:30.233 --> 06:31.567
-Can I get out and like--
-No.

06:31.600 --> 06:33.467
-I didn't
do anything wrong, dude.

06:33.500 --> 06:35.833
-Okay. So you were trying
to use a screwdriver
to force it open?

06:35.867 --> 06:38.533
-No, I didn't know that.
I had my keys right here, dude.

06:38.567 --> 06:40.400
Just don't take me
to jail, please.

06:40.433 --> 06:42.900
I'll just (bleep) bail, dude.

06:42.933 --> 06:45.767
I'll just walk
way far away, dude, please?

06:45.800 --> 06:47.700
-Okay.
-I can't do it.

06:47.733 --> 06:49.100
-Do you want
to say goodbye to your dog?

06:50.433 --> 06:51.733
All right.

06:51.767 --> 06:55.067
-(sniffing) Rascal?

06:55.067 --> 06:58.467
Love you, baby.
Don't take me to jail, please.
-(Rascal growls)

06:58.500 --> 06:59.667
-All right.
-Please?

06:59.700 --> 07:01.833
You can't do this to me, man.

07:01.867 --> 07:03.433
-I can understand
you miss your dog.

07:08.333 --> 07:10.267
-I recently found out
I was gonna be a father again.

07:10.300 --> 07:12.133
Got a new family coming.

07:12.167 --> 07:14.067
A two-year-old,
another one on the way.

07:14.067 --> 07:16.067
It makes you appreciate
the little things in life.

07:16.067 --> 07:17.967
Makes you kind
of take a step back,

07:18.067 --> 07:19.733
see the bigger picture.

07:19.767 --> 07:25.200
And enjoy the time you get
to spend with your family
when you're not here at work.

07:25.233 --> 07:27.067
-(radio beeps)
-4301, dispatch.

07:27.067 --> 07:28.867
I'll take that call,
Wrightsboro at Jackson.

07:28.900 --> 07:31.500
We're to assist
Crime Suppression
with a traffic stop.

07:31.533 --> 07:35.767
Please request another unit
for a search of a vehicle.

07:38.300 --> 07:40.133
-What's up?
-What's up?

07:40.167 --> 07:41.900
-(indistinct chatter)

07:43.300 --> 07:44.767
-Put your cigarette out.

07:46.867 --> 07:48.700
Do you have anything on you
I need to know about?

07:48.733 --> 07:49.800
-No, sir.

07:49.833 --> 07:51.100
-Right here.

07:51.133 --> 07:52.433
Look the other way.

07:57.667 --> 07:59.433
-So I'm gonna ask you
something real quick, okay?

07:59.467 --> 08:00.933
-Okay.
