what's going on,

12:52.500 --> 12:55.767
the story behind everything.
-The story behind it is
I was just playin' around

12:55.800 --> 12:59.167
with it, and I wrote the prices,
I said, hey man,
what do you think

12:59.200 --> 13:02.067
this is-- 'cause he
wasn't weighing anything,
he was just--

13:02.100 --> 13:06.267
-Who did you ask this--
this price to?
-Uh, my-- my friend Nick,

13:06.300 --> 13:09.567
he was-- he's livin' over there
off of Boy Scout Road.

13:09.600 --> 13:12.867
-Does he know a lot
about the prices of marijuana?
-Yes, sir.

13:12.900 --> 13:14.567
-Okay.
And you thought
if you asked him,

13:14.600 --> 13:17.100
he'd kind of know
what it was worth?

13:17.133 --> 13:20.567
-Well, I mean...
I didn't really care
how much it was worth,

13:20.600 --> 13:24.267
but I cared how much
the bags would look like.

13:24.300 --> 13:28.400
I'm just-- I kind of like
to be a little creative.
-Sure. Well, here's the thing,

13:28.433 --> 13:31.300
you're goin' in
for possession of marijuana
with intent to distribute.

13:31.333 --> 13:34.267
You'll probably have at least
two different charges
of possession of, uh,

13:34.300 --> 13:36.567
prescription medication
without a prescription, okay?

13:36.600 --> 13:40.400
-With intent, that means
I serve years.
-Correct. But David,

13:40.433 --> 13:42.267
I know you say you're trying
to do the right thing, man,

13:42.300 --> 13:44.200
but you gotta
make better decisions than this.

13:44.233 --> 13:46.633
You really do.
So... I mean,
you're a grown man.

13:46.667 --> 13:48.367
And you know the difference
between right and wrong,

13:48.400 --> 13:49.733
and obviously you knew
this was wrong

13:49.767 --> 13:52.367
before you started riding around
with narcotics in your car.

13:56.800 --> 13:59.733
-One of my biggest pet peeves
is when you see parents
that have younger children

13:59.767 --> 14:02.933
and instead of saying "hi"
most of the time,

14:02.967 --> 14:05.833
you'll hear 'em
tell their kid,
"You better be good

14:05.867 --> 14:07.300
or he's gonna take you away."

14:07.333 --> 14:09.867
And it's not something
that we want children
to think of

14:09.900 --> 14:12.433
when they think
of law enforcement
or see a guy in uniform.

14:12.467 --> 14:15.300
We want them to know
that they can always
come to us

14:15.333 --> 14:18.167
if they ever
need help, because that's
what we're here for.

14:18.200 --> 14:22.667
So right now we're going
to a domestic in progress.

14:22.700 --> 14:26.433
A female had messaged her friend
on Facebook and said
that her wife or girlfriend

14:26.467 --> 14:29.933
was throwing a frying pan
at her or something like that,

14:29.967 --> 14:31.667
so we'll see what's going on.

14:43.067 --> 14:44.933
Sheriff's Office.

14:46.667 --> 14:48.467
Hey, how're you doin'?

14:48.500 --> 14:50.333
-Hey.
-Did you contact a friend
on Facebook?

14:50.367 --> 14:52.433
-Yeah.
-Okay. Can I-- can you
open the door

14:52.467 --> 14:54.433
so I can come inside
and see what's goin' on?

14:54.467 --> 14:56.433
Come out from behind the door.

14:56.467 --> 14:58.133
What's goin' on?

14:58.167 --> 15:02.233
-I was beaten.
-Okay, where's your wife
at right now?

15:02.267 --> 15:04.367
-Sleeping.
-She's sleeping now?

15:04.400 --> 15:06.800
Okay, what happened
with all this right here?

15:06.833 --> 15:10.500
-She hit me.
-Okay. You need, uh,
an ambulance

15:10.533 --> 15:12.100
or anything like that
for any injuries you have?

15:12.133 --> 15:14.700
-No.
-Okay. And she's
in there sleeping?

15:14.733 --> 15:16.367
-Yeah.
-Okay. What's her name?

15:16.400 --> 15:18.267
-Mara.
-Are there any weapons?

15:18.300 --> 15:19.367
-No.

15:19.400 --> 15:21.233
-Mara.
-Shut the door.

15:21.267 --> 15:24.067
-Wake up.
It's the Sheriff's Office.

15:24.100 --> 15:27.100
-Why?
-I'm here to talk to you
about what's goin' on.

15:27.133 --> 15:30.067
-What?
-I'm-- uncover your--
are you naked under there

15:30.067 --> 15:31.300
or you dressed?
-No, I'm dressed.

15:31.333 --> 15:33.067
-Okay.
What's goin' on right now?

15:33.067 --> 15:35.267
Sit up for me.
-I'm sleeping, it's...

15:35.300 --> 15:38.700
-Okay. Did you
get into an argument or a fight
with your, uh, girlfriend?

15:38.733 --> 15:41.133
-My wife?
-Your wife?

15:41.167 --> 15:44.600
-Earlier, I was sleeping.
-Get up, let's go.

15:44.633 --> 15:46.067
Let's come out here
and let's talk.

15:46.067 --> 15:48.667
-I'm sleeping.
-Let me ask you this
as well...

15:48.700 --> 15:50.733
that frying pan
that's on the bed,
is that the one

15:50.767 --> 15:52.067
that she hit you with,
do you know?

15:52.100 --> 15:54.067
Does she always
sleep with that or something?

15:54.067 --> 15:57.667
Or is that just... in there?
-It was-- it was on the floor,
she hit me with it.

15:57.700 --> 16:01.100
-Yeah, it's in the bed now,
it's like--
-I know, she took it with her.

16:01.133 --> 16:03.833
-Okay.
Mara, don't talk to her
right now.

16:03.867 --> 16:06.133
Go stand outside
and talk to that deputy.

16:06.167 --> 16:11.100
-What's going on?
-Go stand outside.
Mara, go outside.

16:11.133 --> 16:12.667
Let me see your arm.

16:12.700 --> 16:15.600
So, this mark on the inside
of your arm, was that
from the pan?

16:15.633 --> 16:18.433
-She hit me-- no, it wasn't
with the pan, she hit me.
-With a fist.

16:18.467 --> 16:21.633
-Yeah.
-Okay, so that's a fist,
what's this mark on your,

16:21.667 --> 16:24.300
uh, shoulder?
-I don't know.
I don't remember.

16:24.333 --> 16:27.800
-And when did this happen?
-Yesterday.

16:27.833 --> 16:30.533
-It happened yesterday?
-Yes.

16:30.567 --> 16:34.067
-All right, Mara.
She has a bruise on the inside
of her arm and her collarbone.

16:34.067 --> 16:35.467
-We had--
-What are those from?

16:35.500 --> 16:40.067
-Because she-- we drink a lot,
and then we get in arguments.

16:40.100 --> 16:43.533
-Okay.
-Yesterday, she had too much
to drink...

16:43.567 --> 16:48.967
-Okay.
-I wa-- I was not
as-- drinking as much.

16:49.067 --> 16:51.500
I had some to drink as well.

16:51.533 --> 16:55.667
And we had an argument,
and she started beating me up
and I fought back.

16:55.700 --> 17:00.833
I went into the room,
I tried to get away.
We both-- it's a mutual thing.

17:00.867 --> 17:03.367
-Okay. Why-- why
are you sleeping
with a frying pan?

17:03.400 --> 17:06.433
There's a frying pan
in your bed, what's up
with that?

17:06.467 --> 17:07.800
-Yeah, to protect myself.

17:07.833 --> 17:10.633
-Okay. Did you hit her
with that yesterday?
-No. No, sir.

17:10.667 --> 17:11.933
-Why is she saying you did?

17:11.967 --> 17:13.667
-I did not hit her
with it yesterday.

17:13.700 --> 17:15.733
-Well, she's saying you--
that you hit her
with the frying pan.

17:15.767 --> 17:19.067
-I did not,
it was to protect myself
from her.

17:19.067 --> 17:21.167
-Okay. Do you have
any other injuries
that I can visibly see?

17:21.200 --> 17:24.067
-No, she lured me
into the other room,
she said "Come here

17:24.100 --> 17:26.067
and we'll talk about it,
come here and we'll talk
about it,"

17:26.067 --> 17:27.933
and she had a knife
in her hand,
and I came into the room,

17:27.967 --> 17:30.800
and she-- and the knife
was there and I... walked in,

17:30.833 --> 17:33.200
and she cut me in my hand.
-And that's how
you got that injury?

17:33.233 --> 17:34.667
-Yes.
-That was yesterday?

17:34.700 --> 17:36.733
-Yes, sir.
-So everything that happened,
it all happened yesterday.

17:36.767 --> 17:37.933
-Yes, sir.

17:37.967 --> 17:40.700
-Well... Mara, this--
this is the deal, okay?

17:40.733 --> 17:44.167
She has injuries on her,
and based on what she's saying
happened and based on

17:44.200 --> 17:47.967
what you're saying happened,
okay, you're gonna have to be
placed under arrest

17:48.067 --> 17:51.067
for battery
domestic violence. Okay?
-Please... please...

17:51.067 --> 17:53.567
-It's-- it's not a choice
I have, it's based
on the evidence, all right?

17:53.600 --> 17:56.400
-Please sir, can I--
can I put my phone
back in the house?

17:56.433 --> 17:58.867
-Yeah, I'll take your phone,
don't worry about it.
-Please sir, please sir,

17:58.900 --> 18:00.633
please sir, please?
-Put your hand
behind your back.

18:00.667 --> 18:03.200
-I'm leaving
for a treatment center tomorrow.
-Put your hand behind your back.

18:03.233 --> 18:06.233
-Please sir, please sir,
please sir, please sir,
I didn't mean to hurt her.

18:06.267 --> 18:09.767
I didn't, why'd she hurt me?
-Just relax.

18:09.800 --> 18:13.133
-She hurt me!
(sobbing)
-Relax.

18:13.167 --> 18:19.067
-Please, sir!
Please sir, please sir,
please sir, I'm begging you,

18:19.067 --> 18:21.967
please sir, neither of us
called the police.

18:22.067 --> 18:24.133
-I understand that,
but the thing is,

18:24.167 --> 18:26.700
is she contacted a friend
who contacted us
on her behalf,

18:26.733 --> 18:29.133
and that's
how we ended up here today.
-Please sir, please sir,

18:29.167 --> 18:32.333
she doesn't want me
to be arrested.
I don't have shoes on.

18:32.367 --> 18:33.500
-We'll grab flip flops for you.

18:33.533 --> 18:35.767
-No, she didn't want this
to happen!

18:35.800 --> 18:38.833
-Listen... in the state
of Florida, the victim
doesn't have the choice

18:38.867 --> 18:42.167
on whether or not
someone goes to jail
for battery domestic violence.

18:42.200 --> 18:44.500
-Please!
-Watch your seat, okay?

18:44.533 --> 18:46.667
It's gonna be easier
to sit down first,
then put your legs in.

18:46.700 --> 18:48.200
Have a seat. Have a seat.

18:48.233 --> 18:50.433
-Why are you doing this to me?
-Mara, have a seat.
Mara, sit down.

18:50.467 --> 18:53.333
-She got me!
-Mara, sit down.

18:53.367 --> 18:56.567
-(Mara sobbing)
-Put your feet in.

18:57.933 --> 19:00.233
-Can I wear a seat belt?

19:02.500 --> 19:06.800
-Kelsey... I wanted to give you
the, uh, Victims Assistance
Program pamphlet?

19:06.833 --> 19:08.833
It has
all the information on there,
'cause you're the victim

19:08.867 --> 19:12.300
of domestic violence.
So if you open up the inside,
it's gonna have information

19:12.333 --> 19:14.300
there. If you don't feel
like it's safe to live here,

19:14.333 --> 19:16.900
um... you can contact
some numbers on there,
get some help,

19:16.933 --> 19:19.133
and stuff like that,
'cause you are the victim
of domestic violence.

19:19.167 --> 19:22.500
They-- they offer places to stay
and things like that
and programs... all right?

19:22.533 --> 19:25.133
-Thank you.
-So... do you have cats?

19:25.167 --> 19:29.167
-Yeah.
-All right. Have you noticed
how bad the ammonia smell is

19:29.200 --> 19:30.967
